     }
     //<-- Add power debug log Feature END
     //=============================================================================
+
+    // NOTE: Bug #627645 low power Feature BEG-->
+    // Update the wakelock disabled state that is held by app
+    private void updateProcWakeLockDisabledStateInternal(int uid, boolean disabled) {
+        synchronized (mLock) {
+            if (disabled) {
+                mWakeLockDisablelist.add(uid);
+            } else {
+                int index = mWakeLockDisablelist.indexOf(uid);
+                if (index >= 0)
+                    mWakeLockDisablelist.remove(index);
+            }
+            updateWakeLockDisabledStatesLocked();
+        }
+    }
+
+    /*
+     * Check if this wakelock shoud be disabled
+     * It should be disabled for:
+     * 1) application uid in mWakeLockDisablelist
+     * 2) not in device idle whitelist
+     * 3) acquired time has > WAKE_LOCK_DISABLE_THRESHOLD (default 1min)
+     * 4) not changed the disable state that make by DeviceIdleMode
+     */
+    private boolean shouldWakeLockDisabledLocked(WakeLock wakeLock) {
+        if ((wakeLock.mFlags & PowerManager.WAKE_LOCK_LEVEL_MASK)
+                == PowerManager.PARTIAL_WAKE_LOCK) {
+            int index = mWakeLockDisablelist.indexOf(wakeLock.mOwnerUid);
+            if (index < 0) {
+                // if this wakeLock is not hold by audio server
+                // and its uid is not in disable list, then it should not be disabled
+                if (wakeLock.mOwnerUid != Process.AUDIOSERVER_UID) {
+                    if (wakeLock.mDisabled) {
+                        Slog.d(TAG, "wake lock:" + wakeLock.mTag + " from " + wakeLock.mPackageName
+                            + "(" + wakeLock.mOwnerUid +") is diabled: false");
+                    }
+                    return false; // not in disable list
+                }
+
+                // handle the wakelock hold by audio server
+                if (!audioWakeLockCanbeDisabledLocked(wakeLock)) {
+                    if (wakeLock.mDisabled) {
+                        Slog.d(TAG, "wake lock:" + wakeLock.mTag + " from " + wakeLock.mPackageName
+                                + "(" + wakeLock.mOwnerUid +") is diabled: false");
+                    }
+
+                    return false;
+                }
+            }
+
+            boolean disabled = false;
+
+            final int appid = UserHandle.getAppId(wakeLock.mOwnerUid);
+            // it should be disabled
+            // for application uids that are not whitelisted.
+            // or special handle for wakelock held by audioserver
+            if ((appid >= Process.FIRST_APPLICATION_UID &&
+                    Arrays.binarySearch(mDeviceIdleWhitelist, appid) < 0 &&
+                    Arrays.binarySearch(mDeviceIdleTempWhitelist, appid) < 0)
+                    /*special handle for wakelock held by audioserver (Be carefull)*/
+                    || wakeLock.mOwnerUid == Process.AUDIOSERVER_UID) {
+                long now = SystemClock.elapsedRealtime();
+                // if screen is off, that is mHalInteractiveModeEnabled is false
+                if (!mHalInteractiveModeEnabled && wakeLock.mStartTimeStamp > 0 &&
+                        (now - wakeLock.mStartTimeStamp) >= WAKE_LOCK_DISABLE_THRESHOLD) {
+                    disabled = true;
+                } else {
+                    if (mPowerControllerInternal != null)
+                        mPowerControllerInternal.noteConstrainAppAcquireWakeLock(now, wakeLock.mStartTimeStamp);
+                }
+            }
+
+            // If not in Device Idle mode
+            // or this wakeLock is not disabled by Device Idle Mode
+            // For shouldWakeLockDisabledLocked is only called when wake is not disable by Device Idle Mode
+            // So here ignore the DeviceIdleMode checking
+            //if (!mDeviceIdleMode ||
+            //    (mDeviceIdleMode && !wakeLock.mDisabled)) {
+                if (wakeLock.mDisabled != disabled) {
+                    Slog.d(TAG, "wake lock:" + wakeLock.mTag + " from " + wakeLock.mPackageName
+                            + "(" + wakeLock.mOwnerUid +") is diabled:" + disabled);
+                }
+                return disabled;
+            //}
+        }
+        return false;
+    }
+
+    // check the wake lock held by audio server
+    // generally, audio server held wake lock for other apps
+    // if all this apps are disabled, then we can disable this wake lock also
+    private boolean audioWakeLockCanbeDisabledLocked(WakeLock wakeLock) {
+        boolean disabled = false;
+
+        if (wakeLock.mOwnerUid == Process.AUDIOSERVER_UID) {
+            if (wakeLock.mWorkSource != null) {
+                int num = wakeLock.mWorkSource.size();
+                int count = 0;
+                for (; count<num; count++) {
+                    int uid = wakeLock.mWorkSource.get(count);
+                    //Slog.d(TAG, "Audio wake lock:" + wakeLock.mTag + " from " + wakeLock.mPackageName
+                    //    + "(" + wakeLock.mOwnerUid +") mWorkSource uid:" + uid);
+                    if (mWakeLockDisablelist.indexOf(uid) < 0) break;
+                }
+                if (count > 0 && count == num) {
+                    //Slog.d(TAG, "Audio wake lock:" + wakeLock.mTag + " from " + wakeLock.mPackageName
+                    //    + "(" + wakeLock.mOwnerUid +") can be diabled for all its apps that it stands for.");
+                    disabled = true;
+                }
+            }
+        }
+
+        return disabled;
+    }
+
+
+    // check if audio server holding a wake lock for the app with a uid of 'uid
+    private boolean holdingAudioWakeLockInternal(int uid) {
+        boolean holding = false;
+        synchronized (mLock) {
+            final int numWakeLocks = mWakeLocks.size();
+            for (int i = 0; i < numWakeLocks; i++) {
+                final WakeLock wakeLock = mWakeLocks.get(i);
+                if ((wakeLock.mFlags & PowerManager.WAKE_LOCK_LEVEL_MASK)
+                        == PowerManager.PARTIAL_WAKE_LOCK) {
+
+                    if (wakeLock.mOwnerUid == Process.AUDIOSERVER_UID) {
+                        if (wakeLock.mWorkSource != null) {
+                            int num = wakeLock.mWorkSource.size();
+                            int count = 0;
+                            for (; count<num; count++) {
+                                int suid = wakeLock.mWorkSource.get(count);
+                                if (suid == uid) {
+                                    holding = true;
+                                    break;
+                                }
+                            }
+                        }
+                    }
+                    // found it
+                    if (holding) break;
+                }
+            }
+
+        }
+
+        return holding;
+    }
+    // <-- NOTE: Bug #627645 low power Feature END
 }

+    private void notifyActivePasswordMetricsAvailable(final String password, int userId) {
+        final int quality = mLockPatternUtils.getKeyguardStoredPasswordQuality(userId);
+
+        // Asynchronous to avoid dead lock
+        mHandler.post(new Runnable() {
+            @Override
+            public void run() {
+                int length = 0;
+                int letters = 0;
+                int uppercase = 0;
+                int lowercase = 0;
+                int numbers = 0;
+                int symbols = 0;
+                int nonletter = 0;
+                if (password != null) {
+                    length = password.length();
+                    for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
+                        char c = password.charAt(i);
+                        if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') {
+                            letters++;
+                            uppercase++;
+                        } else if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') {
+                            letters++;
+                            lowercase++;
+                        } else if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
+                            numbers++;
+                            nonletter++;
+                        } else {
+                            symbols++;
+                            nonletter++;
+                        }
+                    }
+                }
+                DevicePolicyManager dpm = (DevicePolicyManager)
+                        mContext.getSystemService(Context.DEVICE_POLICY_SERVICE);
+                dpm.setActivePasswordState(quality, length, letters, uppercase, lowercase, numbers,
+                        symbols, nonletter, userId);
+            }
+        });
+    }
+
+    /**
+     * Call after {@link #notifyActivePasswordMetricsAvailable} so metrics are updated before
+     * reporting the password changed.
+     */
+    private void notifyPasswordChanged(int userId) {
+        // Same handler as notifyActivePasswordMetricsAvailable to ensure correct ordering
+        mHandler.post(() -> {
+            DevicePolicyManager dpm = (DevicePolicyManager)
+                    mContext.getSystemService(Context.DEVICE_POLICY_SERVICE);
+            dpm.reportPasswordChanged(userId);
+        });
+    }
+

         if (!mFirstCallToVold) {

+                    //       A non-wake up alarm C is set to 10:52:12 with orignal window length to be 5mins
+                    //       Then this will form 2 batchs: batch1 { start: 10:50:00, end:10:50:00}; batch2 { start: 10:52:12, end:10:55:00}

+    //NOTE: Bug #727965 Add for VoWifi calling BEG-->
+    /**
+     * When vowifi calling is in process, there are data packages from cp to AP without target 'uid'
+     * So when doze / light doze is entered, the this data packages will be dropped, this will make
+     * vowifi calling fail. So when vowifi calling is go on, the doze / light doze will be enterted
+     * Here just check the vowifi calling as a condition of entering doze / light doze like screen on
+     * & charging
+     */
+    private class ImsNetworkListener
+            extends AbsDeviceIdleController.ImsNetworkObserver {
+        @Override
+        public void onVoWifiCalling(boolean calling) {
+            synchronized (DeviceIdleController.this) {
+                updateVoWifiCallingLocked(calling);
+            }
+        }
+    }
+
+    void updateVoWifiCallingLocked(boolean calling) {
+        if (true/*DEBUG || isDebugDoze()*/) Slog.i(TAG, "updateVoWifiCallingLocked: calling =" + calling);
+        if (!calling && mVoWifiCalling) {
+            mVoWifiCalling = false;
+            if (!mForceIdle) {
+                becomeInactiveIfAppropriateLocked();
+            }
+        } else if (calling) {
+            mVoWifiCalling = calling;
+            if (!mForceIdle) {
+                becomeActiveLocked("vowifiCalling", Process.myUid());
+            }
+        }
+    }

+        @Override
+        public void setAppInactive(String packageName, boolean idle, int userId) {
+            try {
+                PackageInfo pi = AppGlobals.getPackageManager()
+                        .getPackageInfo(packageName, 0, userId);
+                if (pi == null) return;
+                UsageStatsService.this.setAppIdle(packageName, idle, userId);
+            } catch (RemoteException re) {
+            } finally {
+            }
+        }
+
+        @Override
+        public void setAppIdleEnable(boolean enable) {
+            if (mAppIdleEnabled != enable) {
+                mAppIdleEnabled = enable;
+                if (mAppIdleEnabled) {
+                    IntentFilter deviceStates = new IntentFilter(BatteryManager.ACTION_CHARGING);
+                    deviceStates.addAction(BatteryManager.ACTION_DISCHARGING);
+                    deviceStates.addAction(PowerManager.ACTION_DEVICE_IDLE_MODE_CHANGED);
+                    getContext().registerReceiver(new DeviceStateReceiver(), deviceStates);
+                }
+            }
+        }

+    private static ArrayMap<ViewGroup, ArrayList<Transition>> getRunningTransitionsDebug() {
+        WeakReference<ArrayMap<ViewGroup, ArrayList<Transition>>> runningTransitions =
+                sRunningTransitions.get();
+        Log.d(LOG_TAG,"threadname: + " + Thread.currentThread().getName()
+                                            +  " threadid: " + Thread.currentThread().getId());
+        if (runningTransitions != null) {
+            Log.d(LOG_TAG," RunningTransitions get,runningTransitions: "
+                              + runningTransitions + ",runningTransitions.get(): " + runningTransitions.get());
+        }
+        if (runningTransitions == null || runningTransitions.get() == null) {
+            ArrayMap<ViewGroup, ArrayList<Transition>> transitions =
+                    new ArrayMap<ViewGroup, ArrayList<Transition>>();
+            runningTransitions = new WeakReference<ArrayMap<ViewGroup, ArrayList<Transition>>>(
+                    transitions);

+            Log.d(TAG,"setPosition  x: " + x + " y: " + y + ", the position is  excessive,  so drop it, and set 0. Below is just Trace:");
+            Throwable tr = new Throwable();
+            tr.fillInStackTrace();
+            android.util.Log.d(TAG,"Throw",tr);
+            x=0;
+            y=0;
+        }
+        /* @} */
         nativeSetPosition(mNativeObject, x, y);
     }

+    /* SPRD: Distinguish 3G type icons in Orange for bug 688768. @{ */
+    private int getOrange3GIcon(int dataType) {
+        if (dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_EVDO_0
+                || dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_EVDO_A
+                || dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_EVDO_B
+                || dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_EHRPD
+                || dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_UMTS) {
+            return TelephonyIcons.ICON_3G;
+        } else if (dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_HSDPA
+                || dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_HSUPA
+                || dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_HSPA) {
+            return TelephonyIcons.ICON_3G_PLUS;
+        } else if (dataType == TelephonyManager.NETWORK_TYPE_HSPAP) {
+            return TelephonyIcons.ICON_HP;
+        } else {
+            return 0;
+        }
+    }

@@ -544,4 +544,41 @@
         } while (valueIndex < endIndex);

     }
+
+    /**
+     * Decodes SPDI PLMNs which are stored as nibble-swizzled BCD according to TS 24.008 Section [9].
+     *
+     * Stops on invalid BCD value, returning string so far
+     */
+    public static String
+    spdiPlmnBcdToString(byte[] data, int offset, int length) {
+        StringBuilder ret = new StringBuilder(length*2);
+        int v;
+
+        v = data[offset] & 0xf;
+        if (v > 9) return ret.toString();
+        ret.append((char) ('0' + v));
+
+        v = (data[offset] >> 4) & 0xf;
+        if (v > 9) return ret.toString();
+        ret.append((char) ('0' + v));
+
+        v = data[offset + 1] & 0xf;
+        if (v > 9) return ret.toString();
+        ret.append((char) ('0' + v));
+
+        v = data[offset + 2] & 0xf;
+        if (v > 9) return ret.toString();
+        ret.append((char) ('0' + v));
+
+        v = (data[offset + 2] >> 4) & 0xf;
+        if (v > 9) return ret.toString();
+        ret.append((char) ('0' + v));
+
+        v = (data[offset + 1] >> 4) & 0xf;
+        if (v > 9) return ret.toString();
+        ret.append((char) ('0' + v));
+
+        return ret.toString();
+    }
 }

+void SoftMPEG4Encoder::onReset() {
+    if (!mStarted) {
+        return;
+    }

 status_t HevcParameterSets::addNalUnit(const uint8_t* data, size_t size) {
+    if (size < 1) {
+        ALOGE("empty NAL b/35467107");
+        return ERROR_MALFORMED;
+    }
     uint8_t nalUnitType = (data[0] >> 1) & 0x3f;
     status_t err = OK;
     switch (nalUnitType) {
         case 32:  // VPS
+            if (size < 2) {
+                ALOGE("invalid NAL/VPS size b/35467107");
+                return ERROR_MALFORMED;
+            }
             err = parseVps(data + 2, size - 2);
             break;
         case 33:  // SPS
+            if (size < 2) {
+                ALOGE("invalid NAL/SPS size b/35467107");
+                return ERROR_MALFORMED;
+            }
             err = parseSps(data + 2, size - 2);
             break;
         case 34:  // PPS
+            if (size < 2) {
+                ALOGE("invalid NAL/PPS size b/35467107");
+                return ERROR_MALFORMED;
+            }
             err = parsePps(data + 2, size - 2);
             break;
         case 39:  // Prefix SEI
